HEADWORD: Pimento
<hw>Pi*men"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>pimiento</ets>, <ets>pimienta</ets>; cf. Pg. <ets>pimenta</ets>, F.
<ets>piment</ets>; all fr. L. <ets>pigmentum</ets> a paint, pigment, the
juice of plants; hence, something spicy and aromatic. See
<er>Pigment</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Allspice; --
applied both to the tree and its fruit. See <er>Allspice</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
